{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/12077", "repo": "rails", "body": "> if I find two or three documentation issues in the same file should I submit that as a single pull request with multiple commits, a single large commit, or completely separate pull requests?\r\n\r\nA single large commit is fine.\r\n\r\n> If there's a guideline for when to use docrails and when to use a PR into rails main that would work too.\r\n\r\nhttp://weblog.rubyonrails.org/2013/6/14/docrails-back-to-the-roots/\r\n\r\nAlso, sometimes I get busy and there's a few days lag on reviewing Rails PRs, so don't worry about pinging again until a few weeks have gone by :)\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you for your contribution! :heart:", "_id": {"$oid": "5237cf27bd3543c151007b03"}, "issue_id": 12077, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/23809228", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/12077#issuecomment-23809228", "updated_at": "2013-09-04T17:44:28Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "login": "steveklabnik", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users